#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/basics/translation,_rotation,_scale.rst:5
msgid "Translation, Rotation, Scale"
msgstr "移動、回転、拡大/縮小"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/basics/translation,_rotation,_scale.rst:7
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "リファレンス"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/basics/translation,_rotation,_scale.rst:16
msgid ""
"Once you have a selection of one or more elements, you can grab/move "
"(:kbd:`G`), rotate (:kbd:`R`) or scale (:kbd:`S`) them, like many other "
"things in Blender, as described in the :doc:`Manipulation in 3D Space "
"</3d_interaction/transformations/basics>` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/basics/translation,_rotation,_scale.rst:18
msgid ""
"To move, rotate and scale selected components, either use the "
":guilabel:`Translate`, :guilabel:`Rotate`, and :guilabel:`Scale` buttons, "
"the :doc:`transform manipulators "
"</3d_interaction/transform_control/manipulators>`, or the shortcuts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/basics/translation,_rotation,_scale.rst:20
msgid ""
":kbd:`G`, :kbd:`R`, and :kbd:`S` respectively. After moving a selection, the"
" options in the Tool Shelf allow you to fine-tune your changes, limit the "
"effect to certain axes, turn proportional editing on and off, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/basics/translation,_rotation,_scale.rst:24
msgid ""
"Of course, when you move an element of a given type (e.g. an edge), you also"
" modify the implicitly related elements of other kinds (e.g. vertices and "
"faces)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/basics/translation,_rotation,_scale.rst:27
msgid ""
"You also have in :guilabel:`Edit` mode an extra option when using these "
"basic manipulations: the :doc:`proportional editing "
"</3d_interaction/transform_control/proportional_edit>`."
msgstr ""
